AXON: Encyclopedia Filesystem for TaijiOS

A file-based AI system focused on transparency and self-documentation. AXON
implements a knowledge base exposed through the 9P protocol where entries,
citations, and search are all accessed as file operations.

OVERVIEW

AXON provides a transparent, file-based encyclopedia following Plan 9's
"everything is a file" philosophy:

    9P Filesystem       - Complete encyclopedia exposed via 9P
    Entry Management    - Create, read, update knowledge entries
    Search              - Full-text search via file operations
    Citation Tracking   - Track sources and provenance
    Memory Systems      - Episodic, semantic, procedural memory
    Document Ingestion  - Parse txt, md, pdf; extract facts

Architecture:

    ┌───────────────────────────────────────────────┐
    │              AXON Server                      │
    │  • Encyclopedia  • Search  • Memory           │
    │  • Ingest Pipeline  • Citation Tracking       │
    └───────────────────┬───────────────────────────┘
                        │ 9P/TCP
                        ↓
                ┌───────────────┐
                │   Marrow      │
                │  /mnt/axon    │
                └───────────────┘

QUICK START

Build and run:

    mk axon-build
    ./bin/axon -p 17020 -d ./axon/data

Interact via filesystem:

    9p -a localhost!17020 mount /mnt/axon
    cat /mnt/axon/status
    echo "add_entry 'Title' 'Content...'" > /mnt/axon/ctl
    echo "search term" > /mnt/axon/encyclopedia/search/query
    cat /mnt/axon/encyclopedia/search/results

FILESYSTEM LAYOUT

/axon/
├── ctl                   # Control file (write commands)
├── status                # Status information (read)
├── encyclopedia/
│   ├── entries/          # Knowledge entries
│   ├── search/
│   │   ├── query        # Write: search query
│   │   └── results      # Read: search results
│   ├── confidence/       # Confidence scores
│   ├── contradictions/   # Unresolved conflicts
│   └── sources/          # Source documents
├── memory/
│   ├── episodic/         # Conversation history
│   ├── semantic/         # Facts and entities
│   └── procedural/       # Learned skills
└── ingest/               # Document ingestion
    ├── queue             # Queue of documents to process
    ├── status            # Ingestion status
    └── sources/          # Registered sources

CONTROL COMMANDS

Write commands to /ctl:

    add_entry <title> <content>    - Create new entry
    add_source <path>              - Add document source
    search <query>                 - Search entries
    status                         - Get status info
    sync                           - Sync to disk

COMPONENTS

lib/encyclopedia/    - Core encyclopedia functionality
lib/fs/             - 9P filesystem implementation
lib/ingest/         - Document ingestion pipeline
lib/memory/         - Memory systems
cmd/axon/           - Main server executable
include/            - Public headers
data/               - Runtime data storage

BUILD

Requires TaijiOS toolchain (Plan 9 compilers):

    mk toolchain      - Build toolchain first
    mk axon-build     - Build AXON module
    mk all           - Build all TaijiOS components

Binary: bin/axon

CONFIGURATION

Command-line options:

    -a address       - Address to bind to (default: all interfaces)
    -p port          - Port to listen on (default: 17020)
    -d datadir       - Data directory path (default: ./data)

DATA FORMAT

Entries are stored as markdown files with metadata:

    # Title

    Confidence: 0.95

    Entry content here...

EXAMPLES

Start AXON:

    ./bin/axon

Search for entries:

    echo "Eiffel" > /mnt/axon/encyclopedia/search/query
    cat /mnt/axon/encyclopedia/search/results

Read an entry:

    cat /mnt/axon/encyclopedia/entries/Eiffel_Tower

Use standard tools:

    grep -r "Paris" /mnt/axon/encyclopedia/entries/
    find /mnt/axon/encyclopedia/confidence -type f | xargs cat

INTEGRATION

AXON integrates with Marrow's service registry for automatic discovery.
Register as a service for other TaijiOS components to mount.

FUTURE PHASES

    Document Ingestion - PDF parsing, fact extraction
    Semantic Memory    - Entity extraction, knowledge graph
    Episodic Memory    - Conversation storage
    Self-Documentation - Automatic change logging
    Contradiction Detection
    Inference Integration
    Streaming Updates
    Kryon Integration   - GUI visualization
